{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a5002906-072d-44c8-8a37-8f4a6023eed3","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b79c1e97-84d9-4b9f-bcdc-31f81ee88200","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"CFD5:33D9D0:14B7659:17F9B3A:69EC1324"},"id":"28cdbd61-7295-45c8-aff7-6fe8cbdbdef0","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:04:42.805Z","parentId":"40a80138-2184-4983-b91a-8ba09f0fc4bb"}
